From: appliance-os <appliance-os@localhost>
Subject: [PATCH] wayland: treat configure as implicit scale=1.0 when fractional scale is unavailable

jfn_wl_scale_known() gates the entire VO startup sequence. It only
returns true after a wp_fractional_scale_v1.preferred_scale event sets
WINDOW_STATE.scale. On compositors that don't advertise
wp_fractional_scale_manager_v1 (Weston < 14.0, Cage, etc.), this event
never fires, and the application hangs forever in wait_for_vo_window().

All downstream consumers already default to scale 1.0 when the scale
sentinel is unset (jfn_wl_get_cached_scale returns 1.0, PendingConfigure
defaults scale_120 to 120, CEF's cached_scale returns 1.0). The only
place that doesn't is this gate.

Fall back: if the compositor has sent an xdg_toplevel.configure (meaning
window_size_known is true), it has committed to a geometry. Without
fractional scale, the implicit scale is 1.0. Let the app proceed.

---
 src/wayland/src/proxy.rs | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/wayland/src/proxy.rs b/src/wayland/src/proxy.rs
index 0000000..0000001 100644
--- a/src/wayland/src/proxy.rs
+++ b/src/wayland/src/proxy.rs
@@ -68,7 +68,7 @@ extern "C" fn on_scale(scale_120: c_int) {
 }

 pub fn jfn_wl_scale_known() -> bool {
-    WINDOW_STATE.scale() > 0.0
+    WINDOW_STATE.scale() > 0.0 || jfn_wl_window_size_known()
 }

 pub fn jfn_wl_get_cached_scale() -> f32 {
